31/10/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- The government is finalising work on a new draft law to prevent conflicts of interest. At the weekend, an adviser to Prime Minister Sali Berisha, Fatbardh Kadilli, issued a statement saying the law includes tougher measures for boosting transparency and combatting corruption. 
In other news, police announced that four members of the Tirana Rapid Deployment Unit were arrested on Saturday for suspected abuse of office. Prosecutors say they were involved in an armed robbery earlier this month. (Albanian News - 31/10/05)
